OL,3,CHomeless grandmother has spent 19
OL,4,Cmonths living in Premier Inn
OL,6,FShe said: "My health has got a lot
OL,7,Fworse since I've been in the hotel and
OL,8,FI'm now type two diabetic, which I
OL,9,Fwasn't before. I've also got heart
OL,10,Fproblems, I have fibromyalgia, anxiety
OL,11,Fand depression and it is just getting
OL,12,Fworse and worse."
OL,14,FShe told ITV News she cannot get a
OL,15,Fhealth visitor to give her a care plan
OL,16,Fwhile she is living in a hotel room.
OL,18,FLiving in a hotel may at first sound
OL,19,Flike a luxury, but the reality means
OL,20,Fno facilities for home cooked food or
OL,21,Fa place to clean clothing.
