OL,3,CHomeless grandmother has spent 19
OL,4,Cmonths living in Premier Inn
OL,6,FAnnette cannot praise the care of all
OL,7,Fthe staff enough saying they have been
OL,8,F"absolutely fantastic" and "all go
OL,9,Fabove and beyond" to support her -
OL,10,Fwith one worker, Joseph, even hosting
OL,11,FAnnette at his family Christmas.
OL,13,FAnnette, 50, regularly works in the
OL,14,FRSPCA shop on Bude's high street. Her
OL,15,Fcolleague Sally Swaker says they can
OL,16,Fall see the toll this life is taking
OL,17,Fon her.
